  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the chopped onions and cook until translucent, about 3-4 minutes.",
    "Add the grated zucchini and cook for another 2-3 minutes, until tender.",
    "Add the sliced red bell pepper and cook for 2-3 minutes, until tender.",
    "Add the Korean chili flakes, salt, and black pepper, and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Stir in the cheonggukjang Korean fermented soybean paste and cook for 1-2 minutes, until fragrant.",
    "Add the glassy-jelly mixture and stir to combine.",
    "Cook for an additional 2-3 minutes, until the glassy-jelly has set.",
    "Taste and adjust the seasoning as needed.",
    "Transfer the stir-fry to individual mini-cocottes and garnish with chopped cilantro and a dollop of sour cream or dairy-free substitute.",
    "Serve warm or at room temperature, garnished with additional cilantro if desired."
  ],
